cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the impact of gestures on audience attention and proposes a tool for visualizing the relationship between gestures and attention. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category as the paper mentions using natural language processing techniques to analyze lecture transcripts. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper discusses analyzing eye movement data, which is often used in computer vision research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is mentioned in the paper as the authors use a method called "Time Warp Edit Distance" to calculate similarity between eye movement trajectories. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper mentions using EEG data to infer attention levels.
